3/4 ripe banana, peeled and chopped
1 tablespoon vanilla yogurt
6 ice cubes
2 teaspoons honey
2 teaspoons flaxseed oil
Combine the apple juice, peach, banana, yogurt, and ice in a blender and puree until smooth. Add the honey
and flaxseed oil and puree briefly to incorporate.
Pour into glasses and serve right away.Breakfast Fried Rice with Scrambled EggsThink outside the (cereal) box: fried rice is a great way to fuel up with carbs in the morning. With brown rice, lots of fresh vegetables, and a minimal amount of fat, this recipe is a healthy take on fried rice and is high in vitamin B6. <em>Lop chong</em> is a dried, cooked Chinese sausage with a slightly sweet and smoky flavor; it will require a trip to the Asian grocery store, but you can choose to leave it out. Breakfast Fried Rice with Scrambled EggsMAKES 4 SERVINGS
Fried Rice
2 tablespoons chopped lop chong (Chinese sausage; optional)
